   <h2 align="center">Overview</h2>
   <hr>
   <br><br>


   <h3 align="center">Platform</h3>


   <p><b>Plazma Framework</b> is foundation for creating business solution.


   <p><b>Plazma Business Solution</b> is set of solutions.

   <br><br><br><br>

   <table align="center">
   <tr><td align="center">
   <img border=0 src="../images/plazma-system.png"/>
   </td></tr>
   </table>


   <p><b>Plazma Framework</b> has two parties: <b>Core</b> , <b>Client</b>
<br><br><br><br>
   <p><b>What is Framework Core?</b>

   <p><b>Configuration</b>
   <ul>
     <li>Entities
     <li>Actions
     <li>Menu Bar
     <li>Tool Bar
     <li>Forms
     <li>Reports
     <li>Other objects
   </ul>

   <p><b>Integration</b>
   <ul>
     <li>Services (Spring)
     <li>Security (Spring Security)
     <li>Plazma ERM (ORM)
     <li>Reporting System (JasperReports)
   </ul>

   <p><b>Management</b>
   <ul>
     <li>Configuration Management
     <li>Service Management
     <li>Association Management
     <li>Report Management. Report Storage
   </ul>

   <br><br>
   <p><b>What is Framework Client?</b>

   <p><b>Integration</b>
   <ul>
     <li>Execute Actions
     <li>Execute Services
     <li>Execute Reports
   </ul>

   <p><b>Implementation</b>
   <ul>
     <li>UI (User Interface)
      <ul>
        <li>Menu Bar
        <li>Tool Bar
        <li>Forms
        <li>Dialogs
        <li>UI Controls
        <li>Other UI components
      </ul>
   </ul>

   

   <br><br><br><br>
   <h3 align="center">Architecture</h3>

   <p>The System is presented in three variants.
      
   <p>1. <b>Desktop Client -> Database Server</b>
   <p>2. <b>Desktop Client -> Application Server -> Database Server</b>
   <p>3. <b>Web Client -> Web Server -> Database Server</b>
   
   <br><br><br><br>
   <h3 align="center">Client</h3>

   <p>Client side has two variants: <b>Desktop Client</b> è <b>Web Client</b>.

   <p><b>Desktop Client</b> - Desktop Application.

   <p><b>Web Client</b> - Internet browser.



   <br><br><br><br>
   <h3 align="center">Server</h3>

   <p>Server side consists of several components:

  <ul>
    <li>Database Server
    <li>Application Server
    <li>Web Server <b><sup><font color="red">*</font></sup></b>
  </ul>



   <br><br>
   <h3 align="center">Modules</h3>

   <p>The System consists of several modules. Each module can be replaced or disabled. 
    You can reconfigure the module or modify source code of the module.

  

